    "media:imagetext": "AIRONAUTICA\nBOEING 747SP-38 C.N. 22672?537. VH-EAB. 'City of\nWinton', VH-EAB is the second of the two Rolls Royce\npowered 'Special Performance' 747 airplanes for Qantas.\nThey are operated on routes to Wellington in New Zealand\nas well as from Brisbane and Townsville to Honolulu and\nfrom Brisbane to Manilla. As seen, VH-EAB is displaying\ntitles relating to the 1982 Commonwealth Games in Brisbane.\nA Merv Dicks photo.\nAIRONAUTICA, P.O. BOX 54, POTTS POINT, N.S.W. 2011, AUSTRALIA.\nUSA \u0026 EEC Distribution by Aviation World, P.O. Box 188, Bethel, Conn. 06801\nAFFIX\nSTAMP\nHERE\nRe PC-005\n2001.106.270",
